"What's fascinating is how added grapefruit harmonizes and resonates with the beer's base flavors. Grapefruit is a common adjective of hoppy brew, but it's really just how your palate interprets and parses the spectrum of flavors in an hop-forward ale. Adding grapefruit proves there is some molecular similarity in how hopped ale and bitter citrus affect your palate. Bitter rind against tangy sweetness amplify the bitter-sweet duality inherent in beer...after reviewing IPA's for so long it's interesting how many times the first flavor that came to mind was grapefruit."
